CITY OF DOVER, DELAWARE SETTLEMENT RATE SCHEDULE REACTIVE POWER SERVICE FROM THE VANSANT FACILITY
The City of Dover, Delaware ("Dover") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the VanSant electric power generation facility (the "Project") to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This rate schedule sets forth Dover's revenue requirements for providing Reactive Supply Service from the Project to PJM as contemplated by' Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Supply Services.
Total charges for any twelve-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This rate schedule is effective on June 1, 2021.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Units Annual Revenue Requirement Monthly Revenue Requirement
Van Sant $19,531.40 $1,627.62
